<TITLE> BELA's Syeda Rizwana Hasan gets Goldman Prize </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 19 (bdnews24.com)Chief executive of Bangladesh Environment Lawyers Association (BELA) Syeda Rizwana Hasan has been awarded the Goldman Environmental Prize, the world's largest prize to honour individual environmentalists. The prestigious US-based prize, with a financial award of $150,000, is given to six environmentalists from six continents annually. Rizwana has been awarded for her contribution to the development and preservation of the environment, a statement said Sunday. She is the first Bangladeshi to receive the prize for her decisive legal battles against the toxic ship breaking industry, to preserve the environment and the interests of the workers. Apart from Rizwana, other prize winners are Mark Ona Essangui from Gabon, Olga Speranskaya from Russia, Yuyun Isamawati from Indonesia and Wanze Eduards and Hugo Jabini from Surinam. The Goldman Prize was introduced by San Francisco-based philanthropist Richard N Goldman and his late wife Rhonda H Goldman in 1989. Some 133 persons from 75 countries have received the prize to date for their outstanding work in support of the environment. bdnew
